       <text id="B0002T">
              <front id="d2">
                     <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                            <p>Durborau writes Jackson concerning a meeting about a lot.</p>
                     </div1>
              </front>

              <body id="d4">
                     <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                            <head>
                                   <name type="recipient">Thomas P. Jackson</name>
                            </head>

                            <opener>
                                   <dateline>
                                          <date value="1867-08-22"><abbr expan="August">Aug<hi
                                                  rend="super">t</hi></abbr> 22<hi
                                                  rend="super">d</hi> 1867 </date>
                                          <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                                   </dateline>
                                   <salute>Sir,</salute>
                            </opener>

                            <p>I have this moment saw Mr. Potter and he desires me to say that he
                                   will be in Staunton Tuesday 27<hi rend="super">th</hi> inst. to
                                   arrange matters with you concerning the Lot.</p>

                            <closer>
                                   <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                                   <signed>
                                          <hi rend="underline">D. D. Durborau</hi>
                                   </signed>
                            </closer>
                     </div1>
              </body>
       </text>
